  {
    q: "Do you handle PLC / control system failures on industrial machines?",
    a: "Yes. Industrial machines use programmable logic controllers (PLCs), often Allen-Bradley or Siemens, with custom HMI panels. Diagnostic requires PLC-specific knowledge and the original program backup. We coordinate with the manufacturer's authorized service network for proprietary firmware while handling field hardware swap and electrical service. Typical PLC service runs $1,800 to $3,500 depending on whether the program survived or needs reload."
  },
